$ Registry: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Office\16.0\Word\Options

{ SQLSecurityCheck

  The value of `SQLSecurityCheck` controls whether opening a → Microsoft/Office/Word[Word] document with a → Microsoft/Office/Word/Object-Model/MailMerge[MailMerge] causes a message box with the
  warning *Microsoft/Office/Word/Object-Model/MailMerge*.

  If `SQLSecurityCheck` is set to 0, the warning will not be issued.

  See also → https://support.microsoft.com/en-au/help/825765/you-receive-the-opening-this-will-run-the-following-sql-command-messag[support.microsoft.com / 825765].

}
{ DeveloperTools #reg-word-developer-tools

  If the value of `DeveloperTools` is set to 1, Word → Microsoft/Office/Excel#excel-display-developer-tab[displays the developer tools] (which is required(?) to record macros).

  Compare with the same value under → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Excel/Options#reg-excel-developer-tools[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Office\_version_\Excel\Options`].

}
{ Setting these options with PowerShell

  The following → Windows/PowerShell script sets some of the options that are found under this → Windows/registry/tree-structure/key[registry key]:
  gh|about-Windows-Registry|/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Word/Options/setOptions.ps1||

}
sa:
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Word[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Office\X.Y\Word`]
